From: ChatDBG Pro bench
Subject: [inject] drop zero-init of mg_http_message in mg_http_parse

Upstream mg_http_parse() starts with `memset(hm, 0, sizeof(*hm));`
so that fields the parser never writes (empty body, unused header
slots, missing query string) read as deterministic zero. This patch
removes that memset. On a short request that leaves optional fields
untouched, a downstream reader sees uninitialized stack memory and
MSan flags the access.

NOTE: line numbers are approximate vs. Mongoose 7.15. Step 4 re-bases
this before `git apply`.

---
 mongoose.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mongoose.c b/mongoose.c
--- a/mongoose.c
+++ b/mongoose.c
@@ int mg_http_parse(const char *s, size_t len, struct mg_http_message *hm)
 int mg_http_parse(const char *s, size_t len, struct mg_http_message *hm) {
   int is_response, req_len = mg_http_get_request_len((unsigned char *) s, len);
-  memset(hm, 0, sizeof(*hm));
   if (req_len <= 0) return req_len;
